@danmoseley

The ideal fix looks like
```ts
// From
import type { Foo } from "./bar";
// to
import { Baz, type Foo } from "./bar";
```
but it kept coming back to a fix that produces
```ts
// From
import type { Foo } from "./bar";
// to
import type { Foo } from "./bar";
import { Baz } from "./bar";
```
I think it's confused because of how synthesized completion members interact with bracket vs dot notation. The likely fix is probably in completions.ts, not importFixes.

